Yugoslavia has signed up for a 550 mlnECU loan from the European Community (EC), the  official Tanjugnews agency said.    It said the agreement, which has yet to be ratified by the12 EC countries and the European Parliament, was signed lastnight in Brussels.    The 20 year, 7.5 pct interest loan will be used to completethe trans-Yugoslavia motorway and modernise the country'srailway network, the agency said.    Yugoslavia's request for a 100 mln ECU grant was refused bythe EC, but will be discussed again, Tanjug added. REUTER&#3;